"nameMeanings":[{"name":"Alice","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Alice Austercarus was born in 1145, in Weekley, Northamptonshire, England, United Kingdom, her father, William Austercarus, was 26 and her mother, Mrs William Austercarus, was 16. She married Walkelin de Dunston in 1168, in Northamptonshire, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in 1173, in Northamptonshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 28."},"et":{"1145–1173":"1145–1173","1140–1172":"1140–1172","–Male":"Surnud","1169–1234":"1169–1234","1120–1145":"1120–1145","1130–Female":"1130–Surnud","1169":"1169","before 1145":"enne 1145","1168":"1168","1234":"1234","1145":"1145","1120":"1120","1130":"1130","1173":"1173","1140":"1140","1172":"1172","Europe":"Europe","England":"England","Northamptonshire, England":"Northamptonshire, England","Dunston, Northamptonshire, England, United Kingdom":"Northamptonshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Northamptonshire, England, United Kingdom":"Northamptonshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Weekley, Northamptonshire, England, United Kingdom":"Weekley, Northamptonshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England, United Kingdom":"Inglismaa, United K